Indonesia Stocks: Aneka Tambang, Indo Tambangraya, Medco Energi

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-08-12T04:56:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-12/indonesia-stocks-indo-tambangraya-medco-energi-xl-axiata.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 11:30 a.m. Jakarta-time
break.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  rose 34.27 points, or 0.9
percent, to 3,903.63, paring its loss this week to 0.5 percent.  PT Aneka Tambang (ANTM IJ), Indonesia’s second-largest
nickel producer, advanced 3.1 percent to 1,970 rupiah, set for
the sharpest gain since March 1. Aneka said first-half
ferronickel output increased 6 percent from a year earlier to
9,838 metric tons, accounting for 55 percent of its full-year
production target.  PT Indo Tambangraya Megah (ITMG IJ), the Indonesian unit of
 Thailand ’s largest coal miner Banpu Pcl, advanced 1.6 percent to
44,650 rupiah. The company’s first-half net income rose to
$205.3 million from $134.1 million a year earlier, Indo
Tambangraya said in a statement published in Bisnis  Indonesia .  PT Medco Energi Internasional (MEDC IJ), Indonesia’s
largest listed oil company, rose 3 percent to 2,575 rupiah, set
for the highest close since June 7. Crude oil futures gained 3.4
percent to $85.72 a barrel in  New York  yesterday, rounding off a
two-day, 8.1 percent jump.  PT Salim Ivomas Pratama (SIMP IJ), an Indonesian producer
of cooking oil, jumped 7.4 percent to 1,300 rupiah, on course
for the biggest increase since June 9. Salim Ivomas reported
first-half net income more than doubled from a year earlier to
885 billion rupiah ($103 million).  PT XL Axiata (EXCL IJ), the Indonesian unit of  Malaysia ’s
Axiata Group Bhd., rose 1.9 percent to 5,250 rupiah. XL Axiata
is seeking a 1 trillion-rupiah loan to help refinance total debt
of 2.5 trillion rupiah this year, Kontan reported, citing
Finance Director Willem Timmermans. Two calls to the company’s
office in Jakarta weren’t answered.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
